annotation.TEXT: I don't think any of those pipes can be entered, unfortunately...
And here we have a fence that looks like vines, along with some fence koopas that are pretending to be vine koopas.
Huh? A 1-up? Then that must mean... This block holds a vine!
Demo count: 3
I just wanted to take a peek in that direction first, before climbing up the vine.
Nope, nothing. I guess I'll go back for that Yoshi coin now.
I just hope that I don't accidentally...

Yeah, there is no sign of the secret exit, and I did scour this level a few more times off screen, and still couldn't find it. I'm really baffled. I mean, this is a red level, so it should have a secret exit...
Garg!
Yes! I reached the P-switch without overshooting it this time! (Actually, that didn't take too terribly long.)
Well, so long everyone, and happy pi day!
Ooh, I see something I can wall jump up!
Huh, interesting. It won't let me wall jump off of the same wall twice in a row without landing, even if I grabbed a vine/fence after the first wall jump.
May as well get all of these coins that I was in too much of a hurry to get last time.
More fine vence koopas. Err... I meant fine fence koopas... Or did I mean vine vence koopas? Alright, seriously, I don't have time to be messing with these guys or mixing up words.
Alright, well since the screen won't scroll any further this way, let's go left I guess.
I so want to check all of those pipes, but I'm short on time right now. Maybe I'll check them on a revisit.
Woo, first try!
Argh! Yep, here come the stupid mistakes, right on schedule!
Likewise, I'm not going to waste my time getting all of these coins here.
Ooh! Got a bonus flower for my efforts!
And that also leads to the defunct pipe, as expected. So, let's quickly go back and look for that secret exit...
...even if it kills me. Oops!
And once again, I'm spending way too much time dilly-dallying!
Oh! Well, that really simplifies things! Awesome! AND NOW THE MOON IS MINE!!! MWAHAHAHA!!!
Yes, it's definitely a fence. You can't punch on normal vines.
The ceiling probably made it unreasonable to try stomping that guy, but a good ol' punch works fine.
Oh, found a hidden block! And, by wall jumping...
But what about the moon? I'm obviously gonna need the P-switch to reach it. Well, you know what? I'll just put down a savestate here, just in case I screw this up.
Just gotta line this up right...
The sign is pointing to the left, so I must therefore go right of course!
Well, there's still one more thing I could try...
Alright, so let's take a look at 2-5, which may very well be the last level left for me to do here right now.

Argh, slipped. But, at least falling here didn't kill me, and maybe I can get back up with a wall jump...
Well, there's definitely something up here. Maybe the secret exit?
...Which I'm going to hold off on collecting for a moment. I want to see if a 1-up chain is possible on these vine/fence koopas.
Oh, yeah. Gotta check every pipe...
Alright, that's enough block-cloning shenanigans for now.
Of course, I've still gotta find the secret exit. It wasn't in that one side area I wall jumped up to the entrance to, I don't think. So, where could it be?
And, once again, the chain stops at 8000. (Though, I suppose I could've achieved a 1-up chain by bringing a regular koopa shell to that part.)
More vines and coins.
Wow, this is going pretty well so far...
...So close...
There's Yoshi coin #2.
I thought there might've been a second hidden block there, even though I only needed one.
There's midpoint. Oh, and don't panic. I didn't spontaneously forget about the vine!
Whew! Wow, I really keep cutting it close with these time limits!
Hello, and welcome back to [title]! Now, I figured a few of you guys would vote, even if I wasn't holding a vote, so let's bring up the results...
You all saw that, right? I so totally had it, but I went too far! That was the one thing I was trying to avoid! Ugghh... Now it'll probably take me forever before I nail it again!

I really hope the secret exit isn't through that pipe. Although, the gray ! blocks have never prevented me from getting anything else important in the past. All Yoshi coins and exits have been achievable even with their presence so far...
Well, if there is a secret exit in 2-5, let me know. Otherwise, I think I'm about done with this hack. I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through [title]!
Oh, so I didn't need running speed to reach the vines from this side.

...But I end up here? Really?! Well, I think that proves that I'm never intended to be able to remove those gray ! blocks in this demo. Otherwise, I'm sure you wouldn't have had a pipe lead to this bonus game trap!

Oh, yeah! There's one more thing! Back in 1-1, there was the P-switch and moon up high in the sky, too high for standard springboard jumping to reach. Let's see if I can do a midair springboard jump to reach them!
Oof!

...and it involves block cloning! I'm going to take an intentional hit here (and not collect my reserve item) so I won't accidentally fry my shell.

Okay, what did that room skip me over?

And up here, we have another vine koopa, or fence koopa, whatever. And, there's also the third Yoshi coin.
Ah, okay. That's where I made my way up, so that pipe didn't skip too much, although I might've missed the fourth Yoshi coin if I hadn't backtracked after coming out of it.

Alright, now unless there's a secret exit in 2-5, I think I'm done... Oh, also... TRS, I did manage to get behind 1-2's goal with tool-assistance, but do you want what's back there kept secret for now, or is it okay if I show it off? Let me know, alright?
